{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:18:25.210006+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my analysis of Issue #5, here is what needs to be done:\n\n## Current State\n\n**`docs/api/errors.md`** currently contains:\n```\n# API Errors\n\nStandard errors use a JSON object with `code` and `message` fields.\n```\n\n**`docs/api/overview.md`** currently contains:\n```\n# API Overview\n\nThis section documents the demo API reference.\n\nSee [Errors](errors.md) for standard error responses.\n```\n\n## Required Changes\n\nThe issue asks to **document the standard API error response shape** and ensure it is **linked from the API overview**.\n\n### 1. `docs/api/errors.md` — Expand with a detailed error response reference\n\nThe current file mentions `code` and `message` fields but lacks a structured reference. The enhanced version should include:\n\n- A table documenting the fields (`code`: string, `message`: string)\n- An example JSON payload\n- A note that all endpoints use this format\n\n### 2. `docs/api/overview.md` — Already links to errors.md, but could be slightly clarified\n\nThe overview already has `See [Errors](errors.md) for standard error responses.` which satisfies the \"link it from the API overview\" requirement.\n\n---\n\n## Changes I Would Apply\n\n### `docs/api/errors.md`\n\n```markdown\n# API Errors\n\nStandard API errors return a JSON object with the following fields:\n\n| Field     | Type   | Description                                      |\n|-----------|--------|--------------------------------------------------|\n| `code`    | string | A machine-readable error code identifying the error type. |\n| `message` | string | A human-readable description of the error.        |\n\n### Example\n\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": \"invalid_request\",\n  \"message\": \"The request body is missing the required 'name' field.\"\n}\n```\n\nAll API endpoints return errors in this format when a request cannot be processed successfully.\n```\n\n### `docs/api/overview.md` (minor clarification)\n\n```markdown\n# API Overview\n\nThis section documents the demo API reference.\n\nSee [Errors](errors.md) for the standard API error response format.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Validation\n\nThese changes would **not** affect the existing validation checks (`make validate`), which only verify:\n- Presence of `README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `mkdocs.yml`, `requirements.txt`, `docs/index.md`\n- That `mkdocs.yml` defines `site_name` and `nav`\n\nThe modified files (`docs/api/errors.md` and `docs/api/overview.md`) are unrelated to those checks, so the validation would continue to pass.\n\n---\n\n**Note:** I was unable to push these changes directly because the provided authentication token has read-only permissions (HTTP 403 on write operations). The changes described above are the implementation needed to satisfy Issue #5.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 784, "prompt_tokens": 10402, "total_tokens": 11186, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 202, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10240}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 10240, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 162}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "9e54ab3b-70d8-4829-b9c0-947bfe5a7d8c", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea42a-53e1-77d1-a966-b64cc7531ff0-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10402, "output_tokens": 784, "total_tokens": 11186, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10240}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 202}}}}]}}}
